WEBVTT

00:01.418 --> 00:03.128
<i>♪ Let's go make some videos ♪</i>

00:03.211 --> 00:04.546
<i>♪ Hey! Hey! ♪</i>

00:04.629 --> 00:06.256
<i>♪ Let's go make some videos ♪</i>

00:06.339 --> 00:08.091
<i>♪ Hey! Hey! ♪</i>

00:16.474 --> 00:17.726
What's shakin'?

00:17.809 --> 00:20.395
Salt and pepper in the house.

00:20.478 --> 00:22.313
I am so excited.

00:22.397 --> 00:24.274
Our first Halloween in Malibu.

00:24.357 --> 00:25.358
I'm surprised
you didn't say--

00:25.442 --> 00:27.610
Mali-boo!

00:27.694 --> 00:28.945
There it is.

00:31.781 --> 00:33.700
No comments on the costume.

00:33.783 --> 00:36.995
Willow was supposed to be
the back of the unicorn.

00:37.078 --> 00:38.705
But she's boycotting Halloween.

00:38.788 --> 00:42.042
Because she thinks
it's cruel to pumpkins.

00:43.960 --> 00:47.005
What about pumped-kins?

00:49.341 --> 00:51.718
Jacked-o-lantern?

00:53.219 --> 00:55.013
Guys, c'mon, this is gold.

00:56.848 --> 00:58.058
Ladies and gentlemen,

00:58.141 --> 01:00.268
your candy testers are here.

01:00.352 --> 01:03.897
Hard candy, soft candy,
sour candy? We do it all.

01:03.980 --> 01:05.106
Just no apples.

01:06.066 --> 01:07.108
Guys, we told you.

01:07.192 --> 01:08.485
We're not giving
you our candy.

01:08.568 --> 01:10.236
You're not actually
candy testers.

01:10.403 --> 01:13.198
Oh, yeah? Then why'd
we make these badges?

01:15.742 --> 01:16.743
I don't know.

01:16.826 --> 01:19.120
Why did you
make those badges?

01:21.289 --> 01:23.083
[all] Trick or treat!

01:23.166 --> 01:26.086
Aw, you guys are so cute.

01:26.169 --> 01:28.088
Here, have some candy.

01:30.048 --> 01:33.593
Oh no.
We forgot to buy candy.

01:33.677 --> 01:35.595
[all]
Awww.

01:35.679 --> 01:38.973
Uh, wait. We have something
even better than candy.

01:39.057 --> 01:40.809
[all] Yay!

01:40.892 --> 01:42.102
Scary stories.

01:42.185 --> 01:43.478
[all] Aww.

01:43.561 --> 01:46.147
Awww...

01:46.231 --> 01:48.983
...some. Awesome!

01:49.067 --> 01:51.945
Stories are way better
than candy.

01:52.028 --> 01:54.030
I'm sorry.

01:56.616 --> 02:01.121
This scary story
is called Frankie-stein.

02:05.291 --> 02:09.004
[Paige] <i>Our story begins</i>
<i>in the scariest place of all,</i>

02:09.087 --> 02:10.338
<i>high school!</i>

02:11.339 --> 02:16.469
And that's how
sciencey stuff becomes more...

02:16.553 --> 02:18.013
sciencey stuff.

02:20.056 --> 02:21.182
The end?

02:22.684 --> 02:25.395
Wow, Coach Carlson's
a really bad teacher.

02:25.562 --> 02:27.313
Eh, it's really on us.

02:27.397 --> 02:29.733
We signed up for a class
called "Sciencey Stuff."

02:30.817 --> 02:31.651
[bell rings]

02:32.235 --> 02:34.362
Paula! Frannie!
Come up here.

02:34.446 --> 02:35.864
I think he means us.

02:38.324 --> 02:40.035
You failed another test.

02:40.118 --> 02:42.454
Sorry about the hot wing stains.

02:42.537 --> 02:45.331
I used your quizzes as a coaster.

02:45.415 --> 02:46.332
Because I'm a gentleman.

02:48.126 --> 02:50.045
There is a science lab tomorrow.

02:50.128 --> 02:52.422
If you don't pass it,
you fail the class.

02:55.925 --> 02:58.511
Oh man. We can't
fail the class.

02:58.595 --> 02:59.596
What are we gonna do?

02:59.679 --> 03:01.222
I don't know.

03:01.306 --> 03:02.682
But Paige did know.

03:02.766 --> 03:04.893
She had a secret
she had never told Frankie

03:04.976 --> 03:06.311
and probably never would--

03:06.394 --> 03:07.771
I build people
in the basement

03:07.854 --> 03:09.522
using dead bodies
and brains!

03:09.606 --> 03:12.776
Oh, I know.
I don't judge.

03:12.859 --> 03:16.112
So I'll turn you into
a super smart scientist

03:16.196 --> 03:19.657
by swapping out
your braaaaain!

03:19.741 --> 03:21.868
And then we'll both
pass the class. Thoughts?

03:23.119 --> 03:26.164
Wait. You want
to take my brain out?

03:26.247 --> 03:27.457
-Can we get ice cream after?
-Sure.

03:27.540 --> 03:28.667
I'm in.

03:31.711 --> 03:34.923
Wow, you're really taking this mad
scientist thing seriously.

03:35.006 --> 03:37.634
Yeah, let's just say
it's more than a hobby.

03:37.717 --> 03:38.927
Get in the chair.

03:44.933 --> 03:48.311
[lisping] Master Paige, I went to
the brain store like you asked.

03:48.395 --> 03:50.146
I got you this super smart
scientist brain.

03:51.398 --> 03:53.358
[normal voice] Sorry, forgot to
take out my retainer.

03:54.859 --> 03:56.569
Thanks B-Gor.
What happened to your back?

03:56.653 --> 03:58.488
Oh, when I
was getting swole,

03:58.571 --> 04:00.615
I must've over-worked
one of my shouldies. So...

04:00.699 --> 04:04.119
[Frankie] <i>As always, Bernie's</i>
<i>lifting stories bored everyone.</i>

04:05.370 --> 04:08.873
<i>So Paige hooked Frankie up</i>
<i>to the brain Bernie brought.</i>

04:15.672 --> 04:16.881
Alright, Frankie,

04:16.965 --> 04:19.009
ready to be
a super smart lab partner?

04:19.092 --> 04:21.177
Yep! Prepare yourself, Internet.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.680
I'm 'bout to memba
all my passwords...

04:28.309 --> 04:29.602
Muahaha!

04:36.443 --> 04:37.694
She's alive!

04:37.777 --> 04:39.988
She's aliiiiiiive!

04:40.071 --> 04:44.034
Behold... Frankie-stein!

04:44.117 --> 04:46.536
You know, 'cause she's smart like
Einstein, but still Frankie.

04:47.996 --> 04:50.123
[grunting]

04:50.206 --> 04:51.332
Why are you grunting?

04:51.416 --> 04:52.375
Why is she grunting?

04:52.459 --> 04:53.960
Uhhh...

04:54.044 --> 04:56.254
B-Gor, what did you do?

04:56.338 --> 04:58.506
Okay, okay, the super
smart scientist brain

04:58.590 --> 05:00.258
at the brain store
wasn't on sale,

05:00.342 --> 05:02.052
so I bought
a monster brain instead,

05:02.135 --> 05:04.888
and used the money left over
to buy this super sweet remote control!

05:05.972 --> 05:07.932
-What does it control?
-No clue.

05:09.434 --> 05:10.852
[grunting]

05:12.562 --> 05:15.190
Great.
Now my best friend's a monster.

05:15.273 --> 05:17.317
What am I supposed to do
tomorrow in science class

05:17.400 --> 05:19.069
with this as my partner?

05:19.152 --> 05:20.987
I'm sorry, what?

05:23.448 --> 05:25.158
<i>[Paige] With the brain store</i>
<i>closed for the night,</i>

05:25.241 --> 05:28.286
<i>Paige had no choice</i>
<i>but to actually study for the lab</i>

05:28.370 --> 05:31.373
<i>and try to pass Frankie-stein</i>
<i>off as her partner.</i>

05:31.456 --> 05:35.752
Okay, the solutions are mixed
and the PH's are balanced.

05:35.835 --> 05:38.171
This should work.

05:38.254 --> 05:42.676
Please don't explode,
please don't explode...

05:42.759 --> 05:44.969
It worked!
It didn't explode!

05:45.053 --> 05:46.930
Coach Carlson, grade us.

05:47.013 --> 05:52.268
Okay, that seems right.
Looks like you two pass.

05:52.352 --> 05:53.395
Yay!

05:54.354 --> 05:55.480
Wait.

05:56.398 --> 05:57.941
Why's that kid green?

05:59.275 --> 06:04.114
Uhh... she ate
some bad eggs for breakfast.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.198
Right, Frankie?

06:05.281 --> 06:06.116
[grunting]

06:06.408 --> 06:08.785
Hey. That's not
her normal grunt.

06:09.744 --> 06:12.205
I see what's going on here.

06:12.288 --> 06:15.542
Yeah, this is a classic "try to
make your lab partner smart

06:15.625 --> 06:17.919
but accidentally turn her
into a monster" scenario.

06:18.003 --> 06:20.839
Whaaat? Nooo.

06:22.340 --> 06:23.466
You in there, Frannie?

06:23.550 --> 06:25.343
[both grunting]

06:27.804 --> 06:28.972
[grunts]

06:29.931 --> 06:31.016
Well argued.

06:32.767 --> 06:34.978
Alright, but I'll be
watching you two like a hawk.

06:35.061 --> 06:39.482
And if I see proof that
she's a monster, you fail!

06:39.566 --> 06:41.860
[Paige] <i>Paige knew she had</i>
<i>to pass Frankie-stein off</i>

06:41.943 --> 06:45.321
<i>as a regular student</i>
<i>for the entire day.</i>

06:45.405 --> 06:48.366
See? Just two kids
at their lockers.

06:49.492 --> 06:51.745
[loud banging and grunting]

06:53.246 --> 06:54.497
[Paige laughing nervously]

06:55.540 --> 06:58.001
Frankie! Wow! Have you
been working out?

06:59.252 --> 07:03.006
Oh thank you.
I would love for you to carry my books!

07:05.300 --> 07:08.970
Hmmmm, that is the way
kids carry books these days...

07:11.473 --> 07:13.391
[Paige] <i>Paige knew the girls had</i>
<i>to shoot a Bizaardvark video</i>

07:14.225 --> 07:16.519
<i>to make it seem</i>
<i>like everything was normal.</i>

07:16.603 --> 07:18.730
Hey guys! I'm Paige...

07:18.813 --> 07:19.647
[grunting]

07:21.232 --> 07:23.068
Yes, you are Frankie.

07:23.151 --> 07:25.320
And we're Bizaardvark!

07:25.403 --> 07:26.654
Hey Frankie,
have you heard

07:26.738 --> 07:28.698
of that new dance
everyone's talking about?

07:28.782 --> 07:31.076
[grunting]

07:31.159 --> 07:34.079
That's right, it is called
"The Monster."

07:34.162 --> 07:35.246
Let's do it!

07:35.330 --> 07:37.123
[upbeat music playing]

07:40.460 --> 07:42.337
No. Hey. No, no, no.
Don't eat the camera.

07:42.420 --> 07:45.465
No, that's--
No, no, no. That's expensive.

07:47.467 --> 07:50.345
[Paige] <i>The video bought them</i>
<i>some time, but Paige knew</i>

07:50.428 --> 07:53.056
<i>she had to turn Frankie</i>
<i>back into her old self ASAP</i>

07:53.139 --> 07:54.849
<i>so they wouldn't</i>
<i>fail the class.</i>

07:54.933 --> 07:57.227
B-Gor! We don't have much time!
What's the hold up?

07:57.310 --> 07:59.062
I can't tell which
of these is the brain

07:59.145 --> 08:00.397
and which is spaghetti.

08:02.607 --> 08:05.527
[gagging and coughing]

08:06.528 --> 08:07.654
That's spaghetti.

08:10.198 --> 08:11.366
Hey girls.

08:11.449 --> 08:14.619
Just wanted to apologize
for not believing your story,

08:14.703 --> 08:17.914
so I made you
this "I'm Sorry" cake.

08:17.997 --> 08:18.998
Hey!

08:19.082 --> 08:20.917
Is that one of them
brain-swapping machines?

08:21.001 --> 08:23.503
Uh... You can't fail us
if there's no proof!

08:23.586 --> 08:24.796
B-Gor, hit the switch!

08:24.879 --> 08:26.006
On it!

08:28.383 --> 08:31.302
Ugh, you're the worst.
Out of my way!

08:31.386 --> 08:32.512
Nooo!

08:40.812 --> 08:41.855
Frankie?

08:41.938 --> 08:42.772
[grunting]

08:43.231 --> 08:44.816
Oh no.
She's still a monster.

08:44.899 --> 08:46.317
No, it worked.

08:46.401 --> 08:49.362
It's just my back,
this chair is killing me.

08:50.989 --> 08:52.532
She's Frankie again!

08:52.615 --> 08:55.160
She's Frankie agaaaiiiin!

08:58.621 --> 08:59.956
Wait. Where's
Coach Carlson?

09:00.040 --> 09:01.416
[Coach Carlson grunting]

09:01.499 --> 09:04.794
[Amelia screaming]
Coach Carlson's a monster!

09:05.712 --> 09:07.339
Meh. At least
we passed the class.

09:08.757 --> 09:11.509
Wait, if the monster brain
is in Coach Carlson,

09:11.593 --> 09:14.387
and I have my brain back,

09:14.512 --> 09:16.014
where's Coach Carlson's brain?

09:16.097 --> 09:19.768
Guess I'm a cake now.
Eh, beats teaching.

09:19.851 --> 09:21.936
Sweet, free cake!

09:28.860 --> 09:30.445
[Coach Carlton's Voice]
Mmm, that was delicious.

09:32.447 --> 09:33.573
Uh oh.

09:39.287 --> 09:41.623
So? Pretty scary, right?

09:43.500 --> 09:45.043
Wait, weren't there
more of you?

09:45.126 --> 09:46.503
A couple kids left.

09:46.586 --> 09:48.505
Because the story
was so good?

09:48.588 --> 09:50.048
And they want to tell
all their friends? And--

09:50.131 --> 09:51.633
Let it go, Paige.

09:53.551 --> 09:58.223
It's time for...
"The Very Scary Hairy Story!"

10:01.184 --> 10:04.270
[Zane] <i>It started as</i>
<i>a quiet Malibu night...</i>

10:04.354 --> 10:06.231
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

10:06.314 --> 10:08.108
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

10:08.191 --> 10:10.276
I love my life.

10:12.445 --> 10:16.282
Hey, Rodney.
Notice anything... different?

10:18.284 --> 10:19.327
Uhhh... new shirt?

10:19.411 --> 10:20.453
-Nope.
-New pants?

10:20.537 --> 10:21.621
Nope.

10:21.705 --> 10:23.039
Move your
giant scissor hands,

10:23.123 --> 10:24.541
I can't see
the rest of you.

10:25.709 --> 10:28.128
Wait... new pants?

10:28.211 --> 10:30.505
Dude, I got scissorhands.

10:30.588 --> 10:32.382
The doctor
who did the operation

10:32.465 --> 10:34.592
says it'll make me
an even better unboxer.

10:34.676 --> 10:38.346
Cool. Hey, I was thinking
about getting a haircut.

10:38.430 --> 10:40.682
Why don't you give me one
with your new scissorhands?

10:40.765 --> 10:43.184
Sure! I don't see how
that could go wrong.

10:46.730 --> 10:49.482
By the way, where'd you go
for the scissorhand operation?

10:49.566 --> 10:51.609
Oh, that crazy doctor who lives

10:51.693 --> 10:53.528
in the haunted castle
down the street.

10:54.696 --> 10:56.281
Oh sure, Dr. Psychoman.

11:02.245 --> 11:03.580
Was the operation expensive?

11:03.663 --> 11:05.498
No, I got a deal
because the scissors

11:05.582 --> 11:07.500
were possessed
by demon spirits.

11:07.584 --> 11:09.627
Good for you.

11:14.132 --> 11:17.677
Whoa... I just got
a weird feeling that we're being watched.

11:17.761 --> 11:20.055
All right, you caught me.

11:21.014 --> 11:23.266
I heard free haircuts
are happening up in here.

11:23.350 --> 11:24.726
I'll take a number three
on the side

11:24.809 --> 11:27.270
and a bald spot
cover-up on top.

11:27.354 --> 11:29.064
[creatures making
strange noises]

11:30.398 --> 11:32.025
What the heck are those?

11:32.108 --> 11:33.568
And if it means
the haircut is still free,

11:33.651 --> 11:35.445
I'm probably fine with it.

11:35.612 --> 11:36.863
[creatures making strange noises]

11:36.946 --> 11:38.448
[screaming]

11:39.574 --> 11:41.618
On the plus side,
we don't have to sweep up.

11:48.750 --> 11:52.879
Aww. A cat! So cute.

11:53.171 --> 11:55.715
That's a clump of Rodney's
hair that came to life.

11:56.007 --> 11:57.217
[creature making strange noises]

11:57.676 --> 11:58.968
[screaming]

12:00.679 --> 12:04.057
Aww. When did we get a kitty?

12:04.140 --> 12:06.309
Oh, right.
[screaming]

12:08.436 --> 12:09.604
Don't worry, friends.

12:09.688 --> 12:13.983
They lived by the scissors...
they'll die by the scissors!

12:15.819 --> 12:16.653
[creatures shrieking]

12:16.945 --> 12:19.572
What Zane didn't realize
was that cutting the hair monsters

12:19.656 --> 12:22.534
only created more hair monsters.

12:22.617 --> 12:27.080
And the next morning,
things got a little... hairy.

12:27.163 --> 12:30.083
Oh, ha ha! Nice!
'Cause of all the hair.

12:30.291 --> 12:31.960
Oh yeah, that works.

12:34.796 --> 12:36.589
[creatures making strange noises]

12:44.848 --> 12:46.141
What's going on, Paige?

12:46.224 --> 12:49.728
I don't know!
Why are we even in this story?!

12:53.565 --> 12:56.026
Time to make a hair smoothie.

12:56.109 --> 12:58.028
Let's give this curl a whirl!

13:01.322 --> 13:03.783
Let's see. Whipped. Puree.

13:03.867 --> 13:05.910
Oh, Hair Monsters!

13:06.161 --> 13:07.203
[shrieking]

13:12.167 --> 13:13.793
Anyone else
want a piece of me?

13:16.338 --> 13:17.797
These things have cars now!

13:17.881 --> 13:19.132
That can't be good!

13:20.258 --> 13:22.260
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

13:22.344 --> 13:24.346
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

13:24.429 --> 13:26.222
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

13:26.306 --> 13:28.183
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

13:29.267 --> 13:30.727
Is that your ringtone?

13:30.810 --> 13:31.728
Yeah.

13:31.811 --> 13:34.064
It's my Aunt Judy.
I forgot her birthday.

13:34.147 --> 13:35.273
Ig-nore.

13:35.357 --> 13:39.194
Wait! That music is doing
something to the monsters!

13:40.904 --> 13:42.113
Give me your phone!

13:44.491 --> 13:46.159
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

13:46.242 --> 13:48.411
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

13:48.495 --> 13:50.205
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

13:50.288 --> 13:51.956
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

13:52.040 --> 13:54.376
The theme song
to Rodney's channel

13:54.459 --> 13:57.754
put all the monsters
in a trance.

13:57.837 --> 13:58.838
It makes sense.

13:58.922 --> 14:01.466
And soon the gang
had a plan...

14:01.549 --> 14:03.343
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

14:03.426 --> 14:04.260
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

14:05.220 --> 14:07.097
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

14:07.180 --> 14:08.723
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

14:08.807 --> 14:10.892
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

14:10.975 --> 14:12.727
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

14:12.811 --> 14:14.896
<i>♪ What, what, what ♪</i>

14:14.979 --> 14:16.856
<i>♪ What's in my hair? ♪</i>

14:18.566 --> 14:19.484
Ha!

14:19.567 --> 14:22.028
Wow, that ended much quicker

14:22.112 --> 14:24.781
and more anti-climactically
than I expected.

14:25.782 --> 14:27.409
[doorbell rings]

14:28.868 --> 14:30.120
[growling]

14:31.871 --> 14:33.540
Rodney, it's for you.

14:35.250 --> 14:37.836
Oh no, all
the hair monsters morphed

14:37.919 --> 14:39.796
into a giant hair monster.

14:41.423 --> 14:43.758
Well, it's over now.
This is how we die.

14:44.801 --> 14:47.470
Come on! What are the rules
of these things?

14:47.554 --> 14:50.306
They go outside and turn
into a bigger monster?

14:50.390 --> 14:52.517
And how did it ring the bell
without any hands?

14:52.600 --> 14:54.519
[Rodney] <i>As Amelia asked logic questions</i>
<i>no one cared about,</i>

14:56.813 --> 15:00.233
<i>Rodney suddenly had a flashback</i>
<i>to the day he was born...</i>

15:03.194 --> 15:04.362
My son.

15:04.446 --> 15:07.741
If you're ever attacked
by a giant hair monster,

15:07.824 --> 15:10.452
use this special hairspray.

15:12.996 --> 15:17.584
Remember... only hair
can defeat hair.

15:20.920 --> 15:23.631
Only hair can defeat hair.

15:23.757 --> 15:25.175
Clear out everyone.

15:25.342 --> 15:28.094
This is between me and that.

15:40.732 --> 15:42.192
This is for you, Papa.

15:56.373 --> 15:59.668
You did it Rodney!
The monster's gone!

16:00.627 --> 16:02.504
I'm proud of you, son.

16:03.713 --> 16:05.965
Also, call your Aunt Judy,
it's her birthday.

16:07.133 --> 16:08.051
Aw man!

16:11.680 --> 16:12.514
[wolf howling]

16:13.890 --> 16:15.600
So, what'd you guys think?

16:18.061 --> 16:20.021
Darn it. Where'd
the other kids go?

16:20.105 --> 16:22.524
They left somewhere between
your dad telling you

16:22.607 --> 16:26.611
only hair can defeat hair
and whatever the end of the story was.

16:27.612 --> 16:28.613
Can I leave now?

16:28.697 --> 16:31.700
If you do, then you
won't hear my story.

16:31.783 --> 16:33.159
I'm good with that.

16:35.537 --> 16:38.081
Well it's good that
the children are gone,

16:38.164 --> 16:42.502
'cause it's time for
the scariest story of the night.

16:42.585 --> 16:43.795
Uh, we're still here.

16:43.878 --> 16:46.715
"The Foam Pit of Terror..."

16:51.052 --> 16:54.014
It was a seemingly normal day
at the Vuuugle House.

16:54.097 --> 16:56.474
<i>Paige and Frankie</i>
<i>were being lazy on the couch...</i>

16:56.558 --> 16:57.684
[both] Hey!

16:58.143 --> 17:00.812
[Amelia] <i>Zane and Rodney were</i>
<i>being annoying in the kitchen...</i>

17:00.895 --> 17:01.730
[both] Hey!

17:03.106 --> 17:05.483
[Amelia] <i>And Bernie was being</i>
<i>cheap as usual...</i>

17:05.567 --> 17:07.610
Sweet. I'm in this one.

17:09.029 --> 17:11.823
No way! A quarter.
I'm rich.

17:14.659 --> 17:16.745
What's happening?
What's happening?

17:16.828 --> 17:19.622
[screaming]
No!

17:22.167 --> 17:24.294
Hey, did you just hear
Bernie scream in terror?

17:24.377 --> 17:25.628
Should we be concerned?

17:25.712 --> 17:26.921
I don't think so.

17:27.005 --> 17:29.799
A terrified scream can mean
practically anything.

17:30.842 --> 17:34.429
[Bernie echoing] Guys!
I got sucked into the foam pit.

17:34.512 --> 17:37.557
Now I'm trapped
in another dimension!

17:37.640 --> 17:39.017
Help!

17:39.100 --> 17:40.852
Okay, we should probably
get involved now.

17:42.228 --> 17:46.066
But what are we supposed to do
in a situation like this?

17:46.149 --> 17:48.651
<i>Do you suffer from unexplained</i>
<i>paranormal activity</i>

17:48.735 --> 17:52.322
<i>in your home, apartment,</i>
<i>or giant beachside mansion?</i>

17:52.405 --> 17:56.451
<i>Hi, I'm Doctor Duckworth,</i>
<i>Paranormal Expert.</i>

17:56.534 --> 17:58.578
<i>And for a very</i>
<i>reasonable price,</i>

17:58.661 --> 18:02.207
<i>I can solve all</i>
<i>your supernatural problems.</i>

18:02.290 --> 18:04.084
<i>Guaranteed.</i>

18:04.167 --> 18:05.377
<i>Prices not</i>
<i>actually reasonable.</i>

18:05.460 --> 18:07.212
<i>Doctor may not be a doctor.</i>
<i>Also I'm at your door.</i>

18:09.714 --> 18:11.341
Hello.

18:11.424 --> 18:12.801
Wow, she's good!

18:12.884 --> 18:14.552
You have no idea, girlfriend.

18:14.636 --> 18:16.471
I'm five billion years old,

18:16.596 --> 18:19.140
but I don't look a day
over three billion.

18:20.100 --> 18:24.729
Now let's see what's going on
with your friend.

18:26.690 --> 18:29.150
Ooh cool,
is this a crystal ball?

18:29.234 --> 18:31.736
Can you peer into it
and see another dimension?

18:31.820 --> 18:35.532
Please, that was
the crystal ball eight.

18:35.615 --> 18:37.492
I upgraded to the ten.

18:42.163 --> 18:45.917
No way, a whole world
made of foam!

18:46.918 --> 18:48.461
I bet everything here
tastes like--

18:49.963 --> 18:52.048
Foam, everything
tastes like foam.

18:53.258 --> 18:57.595
It seems your friend
is trapped in some sort of foam dimension.

18:57.679 --> 19:00.432
Oh my gosh.
How could this have happened?

19:00.515 --> 19:04.227
That is a mystery
we will never know the answer to.

19:04.310 --> 19:07.480
Oh no wait,
this house was built

19:07.564 --> 19:10.066
on top of
an inter-dimensional portal.

19:10.150 --> 19:11.234
That's how someone named...

19:11.317 --> 19:13.194
Liam was able to
buy it for eleven dollars.

19:13.278 --> 19:16.239
He bought this place
for eleven dollars?!

19:17.240 --> 19:19.701
Also every room
is missing a wall.

19:23.747 --> 19:24.873
Oh yeah.

19:26.291 --> 19:27.959
Can anybody hear me?

19:28.043 --> 19:29.878
I'm kind of in trouble.

19:29.961 --> 19:33.173
Hey! You've invaded
our foam world.

19:33.256 --> 19:34.507
You will be destroyed.

19:34.591 --> 19:37.260
[Bernie screaming]

19:37.344 --> 19:39.262
Bernie's in trouble.
Can you help us?

19:39.346 --> 19:42.265
Does a haunted cow scream
at a Kentucky moon?

19:42.349 --> 19:43.892
Uh, I don't--

19:43.975 --> 19:45.810
Does anyone--

19:47.103 --> 19:49.272
In order to save your friend,
you'll need to go

19:49.356 --> 19:52.692
into the foam pit
using inter-dimensional rope.

19:52.776 --> 19:53.818
Great, do you have any?

19:53.902 --> 19:57.447
Does a Kentucky cow scream
at a haunted moon?

19:57.530 --> 20:00.492
Uh... I still don't...

20:00.575 --> 20:02.285
I mean, from your tone
I'm guessing yes?

20:04.204 --> 20:07.791
While Paige continued
to slow down the story,

20:07.874 --> 20:10.877
Bernie found himself
in some sort of foam gym.

20:10.960 --> 20:12.671
[screaming]

20:13.922 --> 20:15.090
Ha, ha!

20:15.173 --> 20:18.301
There's nowhere to run,
Person Made of Human Skin!

20:18.385 --> 20:19.594
Get him!

20:21.179 --> 20:22.639
[Bernie] Nooooo!

20:27.560 --> 20:29.187
[Amelia] <i>In a world where everything</i>
<i>weighed nothing,</i>

20:30.980 --> 20:34.943
<i>the boy who was nothing...</i>
<i>was finally something.</i>

20:36.986 --> 20:38.196
Yeah.

20:39.656 --> 20:41.783
Okay, we need somebody
to hold the rope.

20:41.866 --> 20:46.579
I would do it but I just got
this manicure 50,000 years ago.

20:47.872 --> 20:49.708
Okay Rodney,
you hold the rope.

20:49.791 --> 20:51.668
The three of us will go in,
find Bernie,

20:51.751 --> 20:53.503
then you'll pull us out
of the foam dimension.

20:53.586 --> 20:56.256
Something something rope, got it.

21:00.260 --> 21:01.219
[Amelia]
<i>And so all four of them</i>

21:02.387 --> 21:05.306
<i>made their way</i>
<i>into the foam world.</i>

21:05.390 --> 21:07.559
Wait. What do you mean four?

21:07.642 --> 21:09.978
Hey, guys.

21:10.061 --> 21:12.605
Rodney?! You were
supposed to hold the rope!

21:12.689 --> 21:15.150
I am holding the rope!

21:15.233 --> 21:16.776
Ohhh.

21:18.028 --> 21:20.405
I can't with
these kids anymore.

21:22.365 --> 21:23.241
What are we supposed to do now?

21:23.324 --> 21:24.451
We're trapped down here!

21:25.410 --> 21:27.328
And foam monsters are coming!

21:29.456 --> 21:32.167
[Bernie]
Halt! Stand down!

21:33.251 --> 21:34.878
[regal music]

21:37.422 --> 21:38.840
Bernie?

21:38.923 --> 21:41.217
That's King Bernie to you.

21:41.301 --> 21:44.721
Loyal subjects!
These are my friends.

21:44.846 --> 21:49.601
Bernie, you're the king...
of the... foam?

21:51.061 --> 21:53.229
Yes. And you can
all live here,

21:53.313 --> 21:56.024
with me as your ruler,
for all eternity.

21:59.819 --> 22:00.945
Nah, we're good.

22:01.029 --> 22:02.238
Yeah, hard pass.

22:03.948 --> 22:05.408
Oh, hey. Foam guy,

22:05.492 --> 22:07.369
is there any other way out
of this dimension?

22:07.452 --> 22:08.953
Oh, yeah. Sure.

22:09.037 --> 22:13.208
You're gonna wanna take Foam Road
for about... five foams.

22:13.291 --> 22:15.251
And then take a foam
at the second foam.

22:15.335 --> 22:17.379
But if you hit the foam
you've gone too far.

22:18.797 --> 22:19.923
We'll figure it out.

22:21.299 --> 22:23.677
Farewell, old friends.

22:24.636 --> 22:27.263
Can you believe that
they wanted to save me?

22:27.347 --> 22:28.640
Haha! Me!

22:28.723 --> 22:31.476
The most powerful man
in all of Foamlandia!

22:31.559 --> 22:33.603
Yeah.
And now you're so rich,

22:33.687 --> 22:35.647
you don't even
need the quarter

22:35.730 --> 22:37.273
that's lodged inside
that foam volcano.

22:38.858 --> 22:40.694
There's a quarter
in that volcano?

22:43.363 --> 22:45.407
[Bernie screaming]

22:46.908 --> 22:47.992
[groaning]

22:50.829 --> 22:54.499
No! It sent me back!
I'm not a king anymore.

22:54.582 --> 22:57.168
You know you could just
jump back into the foam pit.

22:58.169 --> 23:01.548
Oh yeah!

23:01.631 --> 23:03.425
Wait for it...

23:03.508 --> 23:05.969
[Bernie screaming]

23:08.346 --> 23:09.639
Aw man!

23:11.099 --> 23:13.435
I think that was
the best story of the night.

23:13.518 --> 23:15.437
Yeah, you told it!

23:16.396 --> 23:18.523
Aw, thanks Frankie.

23:20.483 --> 23:23.486
Well I guess it's gonna be
a Halloween without candy.

23:23.570 --> 23:25.488
[all] Horse-Face Guy!

23:29.367 --> 23:30.785
Eh, he got the holiday wrong.

23:30.869 --> 23:32.287
But candy's candy.

23:33.496 --> 23:34.414
[all] Happy Halloween-mas!

23:34.998 --> 23:37.792
From your friends
at the Vuuugle House!
